latestPosts.caption:
Wait for the DSLR pictures! ✨🧿
.
.
As much as I enjoy getting ready being a Makeup Artist, the process of getting ready as a bride wasn’t easy for me AT ALL! I knew I would be nervous, and I was. Not because I didn’t know what I wanted to achieve but because of the overwhelming feelings that we all have to go through being a bride. 

Just like any other bride, I was RESTLESS, and EXHAUSTED! I had trouble putting on my lenses as I was sleep deprived. I had trouble putting on lashes because of my nail extensions. And I had trouble to work in flow because of the constant calls I was getting as a part of the ‘Indian-wedding-shenanigans’ (read Havoc).

The constant disturbance irritated me as a MUA, and it  usually irritates me when I work over my clients too. But I am grateful to have people in life who took my troubles over them, the ones who sorted the chaos for me, the ones  who said: “Tu tayar ho ja, let me handle the calls!”

And gratefully yet unbelievably, I was entirely ready just in the duration of 1.5 hours, even though we started so so late! 

I am super grateful that I had superpowers in human form! (Not tagging them as I don’t wanna jinx my friendship 🧿♥️)
